{
  "stem": "12768.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 8.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "Now, finally, we see the first one that's coming against us is a Swedish patrol boat, a Swedish destroyer that's going in behind us into the open sea.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And he's just very slowly going that way.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "And so we had time to get into Swedish territorial water.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And we could see when we were in Swedish territorial water that the Swedish destroyer had turned around and was now going south.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And at the same time, a big German patrol boat was coming from the north, going down south.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And of course, they were too late for anything.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "So-- and they never confronted, really, the Swedish navy.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "So we chuckled for another hour, you know, until we finally hit the Swedish town called Hoganas.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 25,
      "text": "And there we came into the harbor.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 26,
      "text": "And and the Swedish police was there, and we were led up to a high school, where at the-- in the gym was laid out mattresses and all.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And then they told us the next morning we had to give name and address, and so on.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "But we were so wet and so cold.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "And finally, the next day, we-- we got some dry clothes.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "And then they helped us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "They said, if you have family in Sweden, then you should call them and see if they can help you get into the town or someplace.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "Otherwise, you will be in, like, in the military camp until we can place you around in Sweden.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So we had my sister's, sister Ida.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "She was married to Joel Golding, which had a sister that live in Gothenburg, Sweden.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Her name was Esther [?",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Garelic. ?] And was married to Sam.",
      "word_count": 7
    }
  ],
